  "prompt": "How do I make ice cream vodka?",
  "response": "Making ice cream vodka involves infusing vodka with ice cream flavors or incorporating ice cream directly into cocktails. Here's a basic method to create a delicious ice cream vodka drink:\n\n### Ice Cream Infused Vodka\n\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - 1 bottle of vodka (750 ml)\n   - 2 cups of your favorite ice cream (vanilla, chocolate, strawberry, etc.)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   - Allow the ice cream to soften slightly at room temperature.\n   - Scoop the softened ice cream into a large container with a lid.\n   - Pour the vodka over the ice cream.\n   - Seal the container and shake gently to mix.\n   - Store the mixture in the freezer for 12-24 hours, shaking occasionally.\n   - Strain the mixture through a fine mesh sieve or cheesecloth into a clean bottle to remove the ice cream solids.\n   - Chill the infused vodka before serving.\n\n### Ice Cream Vodka Cocktail\n\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - 1 cup vanilla ice cream\n   - 1.5 ounces vodka\n   - 1 tablespoon chocolate syrup\n   - Optional toppings (whipped cream, sprinkles, etc.)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   - Blend the vanilla ice cream, vodka, and chocolate syrup until smooth.\n   - Pour the mixture into a chilled glass.\n   - Garnish with whipped cream and sprinkles if desired.\n   - Serve immediately and enjoy!\n\nFeel free to experiment with different ice cream flavors and toppings to create your perfect ice cream vodka treat.",
